<TITLE> JU all set for convocation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Aminur Rahman Russell bdnews24.com correspondent Jahangirnagar University, Jan 29 (bdnews24.com)--Jahangirnagar University is fully ready for its fourth convocation on Saturday, with 3,902 students expected to get their educational degrees. Sixteen among them will be receiving gold medals. Of the 16, four will get Mofassil Uddin Ahmed Trust Fund medals, four Dr Surat Ali Khan medals, two Sharfuddin Ahmed medals and six will receive Asadul Kabir medals. Th university's chancellor, president Zillur Rahman, will hand over certificates and medals to the students at the convocation. He will also preside over the programme and chief justice Mohammed Tafazzal Islam, will address the convocation. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid and Prof Nazrul Islam, chairman of University Grants Commission, will also be in attendance. The university's proctor, Dr Arzu Mia, told bdnews24.com on Friday that all preparations, including decorations and security measures, have been completed. The convocation will be held from 10am to 3pm at the pavilion on the University's Central Field. Rehearsals for members of the senate, syndicate and academic council will be held at the university's Shaheed Minar on Friday afternoon. The budget for the fourth convocation has been fixed at Tk 89,50,000. A managing committee, led by the vice- chancellor and consisting of 50 members and 12 sub-committees, have been formed for the convocation. Three convocations have been held since the university's inception--on Feb 5, 1997, Feb 17, 2001 and Feb 2, 2006. From the university's start on Aug 20, 1970 until Dec, 2009, 17,008 students have achieved their bachelor's degree and 14,025 their master's. In the same period, 154 students got their MPhil accreditation and 200 earned their PhD researcher's degree. Currently, over 13,000 students are studying at the 27 departments and two institutes of the university that has 552 teachers, 221 officers, 565 third-grade and 701 fourth-grade officers. bd
